data <- read.csv("1.csv", header = TRUE, encoding = "GBK", fileEncoding = "GBK")

# 
head(data)
##             
## 1  0.2126197 2.822822 0.9037594 0.21954887

## 5  0.3337990 3.132580 0.8467207 0.15327929
## 6 -0.2064917 0.845098 1.0000000 0.00000000
# 
summary_stats <- data.frame(
  Column = character(),   # 
  Mean = numeric(),       # 
  SD = numeric(),         # 
  Median = numeric(),     # 
  Min = numeric(),        # 
  Max = numeric(),        # 
  stringsAsFactors = FALSE
)

# 
for (col_name in names(data)) {
  col_data <- data[[col_name]]  # 
  
  # 
  mean_val <- mean(col_data, na.rm = TRUE)  # 
  sd_val <- sd(col_data, na.rm = TRUE)      # 
  median_val <- median(col_data, na.rm = TRUE)  # 
  min_val <- min(col_data, na.rm = TRUE)    # 
  max_val <- max(col_data, na.rm = TRUE)    # 
  
  #  summary_stats 
  summary_stats <- rbind(summary_stats, data.frame(
    Column = col_name,
    Mean = mean_val,
    SD = sd_val,
    Median = median_val,
    Min = min_val,
    Max = max_val
  ))
}

#  knitr::kable()  knitr 
#  summary_stats 
print(summary_stats)

# 
median_ <- median(data$, na.rm = TRUE)

# 
data$ <- ifelse(data$ > median_, "", "")

#  1x3

par(mfrow = c(1, 3))  #  1  3 

#

        data = data,

        xlab = "",
